    <section id="introduction">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>This website provides insights into ground-level water data in relation to agricultural practices across various regions in India.
            Groundwater is a crucial resource for agriculture, especially in a country like India,
             where a significant portion of the population depends on farming for their livelihood.
             It serves as the primary source of irrigation water in many regions, particularly during dry seasons when surface water is scarce.
             The use of groundwater for agriculture has enabled the growth of high-yield crops and contributed to food security.
             However, the increasing reliance on this resource has led to challenges such as over-extraction, depletion of water tables, and environmental degradation.
             Understanding the dynamics of groundwater in agriculture is essential for developing sustainable farming practices and ensuring the long-term viability of
             water resources in India.</p>
    </section>

  <section id="importance">
        <h2>Importance of Water Quality in Agriculture</h2>
        <p>Water quality affects not only the productivity of crops but also the health of consumers. Poor quality water can lead to soil degradation, lower crop yields, and health risks due to contaminants. Monitoring and managing water quality is essential for ensuring agricultural sustainability.</p>
    </section>
